  "notes": "Data taken directly from the RFEG rated-recorrido tables (raw HTML parsed) and cross-checked hole-by-hole against mScorecard (meters) and Hole19 — all per-hole distances, pars and totals match exactly. Stroke index is identical across all tee sets. One official quirk: on the Rojas tees rated for MEN, RFEG lists hole 13 as par 4 (back nine par 35, course par 71); on Rojas for women and all other tees hole 13 is par 5 (par 72). The holes array above uses the standard par-72 card (hole 13 = par 5); mScorecard shows the same 71/72 split. RFEG also rates a separate 'Pequecircuito' recorrido (18 x par-3, 2008 m total; Amarillas M CR 52.2/slope 60, Rojas F CR 54.0/slope 69), omitted from the tees list as it is a distinct short course, not a tee set of the main 18. Course ratings (Vc) and slopes (Vs) are as published by RFEG per tee/gender."
